Certainly! You want **discrete scales with named breaks** to use those names as default labels for the secondary axis (unless overridden).

## Where to patch

This should be handled during the `.init()` of the `AxisSecondary` ggproto (or `break_info()`), but ideally as soon as breaks are assigned, to let scale machinery (and user overrides) act as normal.

### Solution

#### 1. After this line in AxisSecondary$init():

```r
if (is.derived(self$labels)) self$labels <- scale$labels
```

insert the following logic:

```r
# If breaks are a named vector and labels are defaulted/derived, use names as labels
if (scale$is_discrete() && (is.derived(self$labels) || is.waiver(self$labels))) {
  if (is.atomic(self$breaks) && !is.null(names(self$breaks))) {
    names_vec <- names(self$breaks)
    self$labels <- function(x) {
      ix <- match(x, self$breaks)
      # fallback to as.character if names missing
      out <- names_vec[ix]
      out[is.na(out)] <- as.character(x[is.na(out)])
      out
    }
  }
}
```

This assigns a labeling function to `self$labels` **only** when the axis is discrete, the user hasn't specified a custom label set, and breaks have names. It falls back to `as.character(x)` if named match fails.

